<html><head><title>Character Art Team Update @ Developers Corner</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EQ Vault</h3><h3>Character Art Team Update @ Developers Corner</h3><p>Cory Rohlfs, Lead Character Artist for Everquest has posted an update discussing the various graphics upgrades that the new engine will support.  Here's a clip:<br><blockquote><br>Along with new NPC's, we are working on the new Epic weapons. We can use the normal and gloss maps to give these a great amount of detail. Also, we are now able to use environment maps to give the weapons a more reflective/realistic look.<br></blockquote><br>Check out the rest of the article over at the <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dev_view.jsp">Developer's Corner</a>.</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EQ Vault<br>News Date: Thu 01 Jul 2004<br>Link: http://eqvault.ign.com//index.php#162<br>Printed On: Tue Aug 24 8:30:42 PDT 2004<br>©2004 IGN Entertainment</font></span>